[thinking] **Exploring Java class compilation**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering whether compiling a class in the org.mozilla.javascript package at test compile time is a violation. I think about using a dynamic Java Compiler, but that doesn't seem right. Given that SecureCaller is public and callSecurely is package-private, maybe subclassing would work, but package-private static methods aren't accessible outside their package. I should check if Maven sources include package tests, but it appears they don't. Perhaps I could use PolicySecurityController?
[thinking] 
