ses. I want to ensure that generated .clazz files in test resources are included in the JVM classpath since Gradle copies them. I’m considering whether adding test resource metadata through reflection could enhance dynamic access coverage, but I’m not sure if we should run this per instructions.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented coverage-focused additions for `org.mozilla.javascript.SecureCaller$2`.\n\nChanged/added:\n- `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/SecureCallerAnonymous2Test.java`\n  - Dedicated test for the active anonymous class.\n  - Exercises Rhino’s secured caller creation path so execution reaches:\n    - `ClassLoader#loadClass(String)`\n    - `Class#newInstance()`\n  - Catches Native Image unsupported dynamic class-loading errors via `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError`.\n\n- `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/resources/org/mozilla/javascript/SecureCallerImpl.clazz`\n  - Test resource bytecode expected by Rhino’s `SecureCaller` implementation.\n\n- `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`\n  - Test-only Native Image metadata for the helper resource and package-private secured caller entry point.\n\nI did not compile or run the tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0363e61edc4a913f0169f52b2c502c81a2b6e0ae44a7035cbe\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 698, "output": 737, "cacheRead": 57344, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 58779, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777675041249, "responseId": "resp_0363e61edc4a913f0169f52b21e3d081a28cb442a611613148"}}
